               <msContents>
                  <summary>Psalter, ዳዊት፡; Image of the Savior of the World, መልክአ፡ መድኃኔ፡ ዓለም፡, commissioned by Ras Mäkonnen, and produced in the Government Scriptorium</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <locus from="1r" to="186v" facs="009"/>
                     <title type="complete" ref="LIT2701Dawit"/>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ‘ǝz</textLang>
                     <note>Psalms of David, with concluding prayers after every tenth psalm (<locus target="#8r #16r #25r #36v #45v" facs="016 024 033 045 054"/>, etc.)</note>
                     <note><ref type="work" corresp="LIT2000Mazmur#Ps118Spiritual"/></note>

                     <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                     <locus target="#186r" facs="194"/>
                       <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወተጽሕፈ፡ ዝንቱ፡ መዝሙረ፡ ዳዊት፡ በትእዛዙ፡ ለርእሰ፡ ርዑሳን፡ ብእሴ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ራስ፡ መኰንን፡ ሥዩመ፡ ሐረር፡ ወዘአድያሚሃ። በ፲ወ፰፻፡፺ ዓመት፡ እምልደተ፡ መድኃኒነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ። በ፴ወ፫ ዓመተ፡ መንግሥቱ፡ ለዳግማዊ፡ ምኒልክ፡</foreign>
                       Translation: This Psalter was copied by the command of the Most High (lit. highness of highness) and man of God, Ras Mäkonnen, <persName ref="PRS5226haylase"/>, prince of Harar and the surrounding region, in 1890 (EC = 1897–8), from the birth of our Lord Jesus Christ, in the thirty-third year of the reign of <persName ref="PRS7006Menilek"/>
                     </colophon>


